# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to share your .python-version.
#   For an app, this is usually fine to prevent.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if target platform varies, it may not be desired.
#*.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, poetry.lock execution is platform-independent and should be tracked,
#   unless you are working on a library/package where dependencies are handled via pyproject.toml.
#poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, pdm.lock is platform-independent and should be tracked,
#   unless you are working on a library/package where dependencies are handled via pyproject.toml.
#pdm.lock

